The paper focuses on studying team dynamics in software development, specifically in the context of adopting new software libraries. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper analyzes data from Git logs, which involves software infrastructure (cs.SI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The study also considers factors such as team size and prevalence on Stack Overflow, which relate to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
